</arg></template></paragraph><paragraph>The<space/><bold>Telstar</bold><space/>is a series of<space/><link><target>video game console</target><trail>s</trail></link><space/>produced by<space/><link><target>Coleco</target></link><space/>from 1976 to 1978. Starting with Telstar<space/><italics><link><target>Pong</target></link></italics><space/>clone based on<space/><link><target>General Instrument</target></link>'s<space/><link><target>AY-3-8500</target></link><space/>chip in 1976, there were 14 consoles released in the Telstar branded series. One million Telstar units were sold.<extension extension_name='ref'><template><target>cite book</target><arg name="last">Herman</arg><arg name="first">Leonard</arg><arg name="title">Phoenix: the fall & rise of videogames</arg><arg name="year">1997</arg><arg name="publisher">Rolenta Press</arg><arg name="location">Union, NJ</arg><arg name="isbn">0-9643848-2-5</arg><arg name="url">http://books.google.co.uk/books?id</arg><arg name="edition">2nd</arg><arg name="accessdate">16 February 2012</arg><arg name="page">20</arg><arg name="quote">Like Pong, Telstar could only play video tennis but it retailed at an inexpensive $50 that made it attractive to most families that were on a budget. Coleco managed to sell over a million units that year.</arg></template></extension></paragraph><paragraph>The large product lineup and the impending fading out of the<space/><italics>Pong</italics><space/>machines led Coleco to face near-bankruptcy in 1980<template><target>Citation needed</target><arg name="date">August 2010</arg></template>.</paragraph><paragraph><template><target>Clear</target></template></paragraph><heading level='2'>Models</heading><table border="1" class="wikitable sortable"><tablecaption>Telstar models</tablecaption><tablerow><tablehead>Unit name</tablehead><tablehead>Model and chip</tablehead><tablehead>Release date</tablehead><tablehead>Games</tablehead><tablehead>Description</tablehead><tablehead>Size</tablehead><tablehead>Cite</tablehead></tablerow><tablerow><tablehead>Telstar</tablehead><tablecell>No.6040<xhtml:br></xhtml:br><link><target>AY-3-8500</target></link></tablecell><tablecell>1976</tablecell><tablecell><list type='bullet'><listitem><link><target>ice hockey</target><part>hockey</part></link></listitem><listitem><link><target>American handball</target><part>handball</part></link></listitem><listitem><link><target>tennis</target></link></listitem></list></tablecell><tablecell>Two fixed<space/><link><target>paddle (game controller)</target><part>paddle</part><trail>s</trail></link>. Games are<space/><italics>Pong</italics><space/>variants.</tablecell><tablecell></tablecell><tablecell><extension extension_name='ref'>http://colecomuseum.com/colecotelstar.php</extension></tablecell></tablerow><tablerow><tablehead>Telstar Classic</tablehead><tablecell>No.6045<xhtml:br></xhtml:br><link><target>AY-3-8500</target></link></tablecell><tablecell>1976</tablecell><tablecell><list type='bullet'><listitem>hockey</listitem><listitem>handball</listitem><listitem>tennis</listitem></list></tablecell><tablecell>Two fixed paddles. Deluxe wood case.</tablecell><tablecell></tablecell><tablecell><template><target>citation needed</target><arg name="date">May 2015</arg></template></tablecell></tablerow><tablerow><tablehead>Telstar Deluxe<xhtml:br></xhtml:br><xhtml:small>(a.k.a. &quot;Video World Of Sports&quot;)</xhtml:small></tablehead><tablecell><link><target>AY-3-8500</target></link></tablecell><tablecell>1977</tablecell><tablecell><list type='bullet'><listitem>hockey</listitem><listitem>handball</listitem><listitem>tennis</listitem></list></tablecell><tablecell>Two fixed paddles. Brown pedestal case with wood panel. Made for Canadian market with French and English text.</tablecell><tablecell></tablecell><tablecell><template><target>citation needed</target><arg name="date">May 2015</arg></template></tablecell></tablerow><tablerow><tablehead>Telstar Ranger</tablehead><tablecell>No.6046<xhtml:br></xhtml:br><link><target>AY-3-8500</target></link></tablecell><tablecell>1977</tablecell><tablecell><list type='bullet'><listitem>hockey</listitem><listitem>handball</listitem><listitem>tennis</listitem><listitem><link><target>jai alai</target></link></listitem><listitem><link><target>target shooting</target><part>target</part></link></listitem><listitem><link><target>skeet shooting</target><part>skeet</part></link></listitem></list></tablecell><tablecell>Black and white plastic case, includes<space/><link><target>Colt .45 Peacemaker</target><part>Colt 45</part></link>-style<space/><link><target>light gun</target></link><space/>and separate paddle controllers. Four ball games, two target games. Special features of the four ball games include automatic<space/><link><target>Serve (tennis)</target><part>serve</part></link><space/>and variable paddle and speed control for three experience levels (beginner, intermediate, and professional). Uses six<space/><link><target>C battery</target><part>C batteries</part></link><space/>or an optional<space/><link><target>AC adapter</target></link>, light gun requires one<space/><link><target>nine-volt battery</target></link>.</tablecell><tablecell>4 lb.<xhtml:br></xhtml:br>17.568 in.</tablecell><tablecell><extension extension_name='ref' name="kaplan78"><template><target>cite journal</target><arg name="date"><space/>Winter 1978<space/></arg><arg name="editor-last">Kaplan</arg><arg name="editor-first">Deeny</arg><arg name="title"><space/>The Video Games<space/></arg><arg name="journal"><space/>[[Video (magazine)|Video]] ''(Buyer's Guide)''</arg><arg name="publisher"><space/>Reese Communications</arg><arg name="volume"><space/>1</arg><arg name="issue"><space/>1</arg><arg name="pages"><space/>17–30</arg><arg name="issn"><space/>0147-8907</arg></template></extension><template><target>rp</target><arg>22</arg></template><xhtml:br></xhtml:br><extension extension_name='ref' name="kaplan79"><template><target>cite journal</target><arg name="date"><space/>Winter 1979<space/></arg><arg name="editor-last">Kaplan</arg><arg name="editor-first">Deeny</arg><arg name="title"><space/>Video Games<space/></arg><arg name="journal"><space/>[[Video (magazine)|Video]] ''(Buyer's Guide)''</arg><arg name="publisher"><space/>Reese Communications</arg><arg name="volume"><space/>2</arg><arg name="issue"><space/>1</arg><arg name="pages"><space/>33–42</arg><arg name="issn"><space/>0147-8907</arg></template></extension><template><target>rp</target><arg>35</arg></template></tablecell></tablerow><tablerow><tablehead>Telstar Alpha</tablehead><tablecell>No.6030<xhtml:br></xhtml:br><link><target>AY-3-8500</target></link></tablecell><tablecell>1977</tablecell><tablecell><list type='bullet'><listitem>hockey</listitem><listitem>handball</listitem><listitem>tennis</listitem><listitem>jai alai</listitem></list></tablecell><tablecell>Black and white plastic case, fixed paddles. The games feature an automatic serve function and variable settings for three skill levels (beginner, intermediate, and pro). Uses six C batteries.</tablecell><tablecell>2.5 lb.<xhtml:br></xhtml:br>13.53.57.5 in.</tablecell><tablecell><extension extension_name='ref' name="kaplan78"></extension><template><target>rp</target><arg>17</arg></template><xhtml:br></xhtml:br><extension extension_name='ref' name="kaplan79"></extension><template><target>rp</target><arg>34</arg></template></tablecell></tablerow><tablerow><tablehead>Telstar Colormatic</tablehead><tablecell>No.6130<xhtml:br></xhtml:br><link><target>AY-3-8500</target></link><xhtml:br></xhtml:br><link><target>Texas Instruments</target></link><space/><link><target>SN76499N</target></link><space/>(color)</tablecell><tablecell>1977</tablecell><tablecell><list type='bullet'><listitem>hockey</listitem><listitem>handball</listitem><listitem>tennis</listitem><listitem>jai alai</listitem></list></tablecell><tablecell>Black and white plastic case, detached wired paddles. Color graphics - each game is a different color. The games feature an automatic serve function and variable settings for three skill levels (beginner, intermediate, and professional). Uses six C batteries.</tablecell><tablecell>2.5 lb.<xhtml:br></xhtml:br>136.57.5 in.</tablecell><tablecell><extension extension_name='ref' name="kaplan78"></extension><template><target>rp</target><arg>18</arg></template></tablecell></tablerow><tablerow><tablehead>Telstar Regent</tablehead><tablecell>No.6036<xhtml:br></xhtml:br><link><target>AY-3-8500</target></link></tablecell><tablecell>1977</tablecell><tablecell><list type='bullet'><listitem>hockey</listitem><listitem>handball</listitem><listitem>tennis</listitem><listitem>jai alai</listitem></list></tablecell><tablecell>Black and white plastic case, detached wired paddles. The games feature an automatic serve function and variable settings for three skill levels (beginner, intermediate, and professional). Uses six C batteries.</tablecell><tablecell>2.5 lb.<xhtml:br></xhtml:br>13.548 in.</tablecell><tablecell><extension extension_name='ref' name="kaplan78"></extension><template><target>rp</target><arg>18</arg></template></tablecell></tablerow><tablerow><tablehead>Telstar Sportsman</tablehead><tablecell><link><target>AY-3-8500</target></link></tablecell><tablecell>1978</tablecell><tablecell></tablecell><tablecell>Black and white plastic case, detached wired paddles, and light gun.</tablecell><tablecell></tablecell><tablecell><template><target>citation needed</target><arg name="date">May 2015</arg></template></tablecell></tablerow><tablerow><tablehead></tablehead><tablecell>No.6065<xhtml:br></xhtml:br><link><target>General Instrument</target><trail>s</trail></link><space/><link><target>AY-3-8700</target></link><space/>Tank chip</tablecell><tablecell>1977</tablecell><tablecell><list type='bullet'><listitem><italics>Combat</italics></listitem><listitem><italics>Night Battle</italics></listitem><listitem><italics>Robot Battle</italics></listitem><listitem><italics>Camouflage Combat</italics></listitem></list></tablecell><tablecell>Four fixed joysticks (two per player). Games are variations on<space/><link><target>Kee Games</target></link>'<space/><italics><link><target>Tank (arcade game)</target><part>Tank</part></link></italics>. Uses six<space/><link><target>C battery</target><part>C batteries</part></link><space/>or an optional<space/><link><target>AC adapter</target></link>.</tablecell><tablecell>5.5 lb.<xhtml:br></xhtml:br>15810.5 in.</tablecell><tablecell><extension extension_name='ref' name="kaplan78"></extension><template><target>rp</target><arg>23</arg></template><xhtml:br></xhtml:br><extension extension_name='ref' name="kaplan79"></extension><template><target>rp</target><arg>37</arg></template></tablecell></tablerow><tablerow><tablehead>Telstar Colortron</tablehead><tablecell>No.6135<xhtml:br></xhtml:br><link><target>AY-3-8510</target></link></tablecell><tablecell>1978</tablecell><tablecell><list type='bullet'><listitem>Tennis</listitem><listitem>Hockey</listitem><listitem>Handball</listitem><listitem>Jai-alai</listitem></list></tablecell><tablecell>In color, built in sound, fixed paddles. Games are<space/><italics>Pong</italics><space/>variants and feature variable settings for three skill levels (beginner, intermediate, and pro). Uses two nine-volt batteries or an optional AC adapter.</tablecell><tablecell>1 lb.<xhtml:br></xhtml:br>211.254 in.</tablecell><tablecell><extension extension_name='ref' name="kaplan79"></extension><template><target>rp</target><arg>34</arg></template></tablecell></tablerow><tablerow><tablehead><link><target>Coleco Telstar Marksman</target><part>Telstar Marksman</part></link></tablehead><tablecell>No.6136<xhtml:br></xhtml:br><link><target>AY-3-8512</target></link></tablecell><tablecell>1978</tablecell><tablecell><list type='bullet'><listitem>Tennis</listitem><listitem>Hockey</listitem><listitem>Handball</listitem><listitem>Jai-alai</listitem><listitem>Skeet</listitem><listitem>Target</listitem></list></tablecell><table